76561198010479045,Recommended,232050,26729264,"Posted: 21 November, 2016",all,Peter Pan,"Eador is a good alternative strategy game to people who are weary of Civilization and its clones, once all the bugs are gone (most of them should be in 2016).It is similar to the old Heroes of Might and Magic and Disciples series, moving units of fantasy setting on a grid battle.Previously, after 300 hours spent in the game, I encountered a game-breaking bug that prevented me from finishing the game. Understandably I was upset and didn't want to write a review. Now after a second attempt at just a meager 50+ hours, the bug didn't occur and I completed the game the way I wanted it.The campaign has multiple endings, and it is a clever way to keep you playing over and over, although it can be long-winded and tedious.The dialogue is often humorous and the various Masters you meet are just as colourful.Eador is a good strategy game to get at a discount."
