76561198004094178,Recommended,232050,16964263,"Posted: 9 July, 2015",all,pmaximus,"A very fun turn based 4x fantasy based strategy game.Dangerously addictive game. Hours just melt away playing this game.It's not an easy game, definately not for casual players. Build order for buildings is very important. You have to balance available money between buying new units and building new buildings/province improvements. Units require monetary or gem upkeep, some require both. Build too many units and you cannot improve provinces or build castle improvments. If you spend too much time improving your castle and provinces the AI will steamroll you with thier army. So a carefull balance between economy and military buildup is necessary.Negative: AI does not calculate battles well. Battles that will destroy your entire army on auto will be listed as being very easy. Battles listed as too difficult are easy to win in manual mode. So most battles will have to be fought in manual, since even in very easy battles you will lose units (possibly even powerfull units) if these easy battles are fought on auto.Pros: Good replayability. Map generator is similar to the civilization games. Large or small shards can be generated depending on desired length of time you want to play in a skirmish.The Campaign is a good way to learn the game, but is very long. I played the campaign just long enought to get the game basics down.Many different unit types available, good, evil, or neutral. As well as magical or mundane units.Overall a very fun game. I would suggest setting an alarm clock before playing since hours can go by very rapidly. I started playing this game in the mornig, next thing I know it's 2pm. I missed breakfast and lunch. Recommended to 4x Strategy game fans."
