,Recommended,232050,27668047,"Posted: 26 November, 2016",all,Tsort142,"*Nominated for Steam's “Game that never stops kicking your b*tt” Award*This game is relentless. Uncaring. Unforgiving. And it will always find more creative ways to humiliate you. Punish you. At first, you think you're such a tough guy/gal, because you've been playing tactical games for decades, so you turn up the difficulty and start your first game. You are told you are a God, and you feel like you'll own this world. You laugh at the tutorial, thinking ""please... this is not my first barbecue here, enough with the holding-my-hand gameplay, give me a real challenge."" And surely these goblins are just cannon fodder for xp right? Think again. They will tear you apart. On your first battle. It's like getting slapped in the face and get told to get back to your seat. You slowly realize how dangerous this first world is. And then it dawns on you : ""Wait... I... actually may lose before completing my first shard..."" Careful planning, pacing, and never under-estimating choices become a necessity. For survival. After a few hours, just when you think you're starting to get the hang of it... you have this strategy all prepared... you have these old units getting tougher and tougher... Then the game crushes you again. It never takes much : it takes one wrong move on the battlefield ; it takes one daring click during a random event ; it takes one management mistake for your equipment or fortress...Soon you're back to the main menu and a lesson in humility has been learned. You click ""expert"" difficulty (default gameplay stats) wishing you had the guts to click ""beginner"" instead... but there's always a bit of pride left in you, isn't there? And then you're off to another b*tt-kicking. This is not a bad thing. This is actually a great thing. Your choices matter. All of them. Because each time you're wrong, you fail. And each victory, each captured shard, is a real hard-fought battle. It's an endeavour. A real achievement. Overcoming the odds. Until that moment when the game will find another way to mess with everything you thought you had mastered, in a way you never saw coming.This game is a tactical boot-camp. Russian style. Be warned."
